description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the post of Consultant Cardiologist (devices/EP or devices/heart failure) available from January 2021. This is a permanent post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will join a team of 16 full time consultant cardiologists. They will contribute to a comprehensive consultant-led secondary and tertiary cardiology service primarily based in the Trent Cardiac Centre, Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust. They will have broad experience in all aspects of clinical cardiology, with sub-speciality expertise in device implantation and follow up.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An additional contribution to either electrophysiology or heart failure service is desirable. The appointee will participate in the 1:10 cardiology non interventional rota covering both campuses of NUH. Full job description and indicative job plan is available on line.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note this job description has not yet received Royal College approval and may be subject to change based on their advice.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Thomas Mathew, Head of service, email: thomas.mathew@nuh.nhs.uk, telephone 0115 9691169 ext:53163&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr T Robinson (Clinical Lead for EP), email: Tim.robinson@nuh.nhs.uk, telephone 0115 9691169 ext: 56248&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr J Chuen (Clinical Lead for Devices). email: Jenny.chuen2@nuh.nhs.uk, telephone 0115 9691169 ext: 56247&lt;/p&gt;
